CSE 5912 Homework #2

Michael Braun

 

 My first edit, I took a random picture of Pele scoring a bicycle kick goal I found on my hard drive and tried to edit myself into it. I took my face into GIMP, cut it out of the background, scaled it down, made it greyscale, increased the contrast and brightness, and added some noise to make it look old. It’s a little smaller than I would have liked and my head is at kind of an awkward angle, but the colors and the blending look pretty decent.

 

 

 
The second picture is of me climbing outside with my friends. I used the newsprint filter in GIMP to make it look like it came out of the news, tweaked it a little, and wrote a pretty stupid fake article to go with it.

 
 

 
The third method I used was GIMP’s illusion tool. It takes a bunch of cross sections of the picture and superimposes them, making this weird hall of mirrors type effect.

 
 
BONUS PICTURE: A developer called Sato has an AI that will turn any picture of a face into pixel art. I took a picture of myself and put it into that tool to get this picture. https://pixel-me.tokyo/en/
